📘 README 2 — Case 2 (Master + Replica + Nginx)
# 🚀 Case 2: Master + Replica DB + Nginx Frontend

---

## 📌 Overview
- GET → Replica DB
- POST/PUT/DELETE → Master DB
- Nginx serves frontend

---

## 🧱 Architecture


Browser → Nginx → Flask API
→ READ → Replica DB
→ WRITE → Master DB


---

# 🖥️ 1. Install Dependencies

```bash id="r2b"
sudo apt update
sudo apt install python3 python3-pip nginx -y
🗄️ 2. RDS Setup
CREATE DATABASE employees;

USE employees;

CREATE TABLE employees (
    id INT AUTO_INCREMENT PRIMARY KEY,
    name VARCHAR(100),
    role VARCHAR(100)
);
🚀 3. Run Backend
python3 app.py
🌐 4. Nginx Setup
/usr/share/nginx/html/index.html
sudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/default
location /api/ {
    proxy_pass http://<BACKEND-EC2-IP>:5000/;
}
🔐 5. Security Group
Allow:
- Port 80 (frontend)
- Port 5000 (backend)
🌍 6. Access
http://<FRONTEND-EC2-IP>
📊 Flow
GET → Replica DB
POST → Master DB
✔ Case 2 Summary
Scalable reads
DB separation

#To check data stored in read replica 

Connect to Master endpoint
database-1.ccvmq8qg23uo.us-east-1.rds.amazonaws.com

Run:

SELECT * FROM employees;

You saw the employee records.

Connect to Replica endpoint
reader.ccvmq8qg23uo.us-east-1.rds.amazonaws.com

Run the same query:

SELECT * FROM employees;

You saw the same records there as well.

That confirmed that replication was working and data from the master was being copied to the replica.
